"<pad> matrix factorization methods for generating low-dimensional word representations have roots stretching as far back as LSA. a main problem with HAL and related meth- ods is that the most frequent words contribute a disproportionate amount to the similarity measure. a variety of newer models also pursue this approach, including a study that indicates that positive pointwise mu- tual information (PPMI) can be used to generate low-dimensional matrices in a corpus. a- - a</s>"